Former Indian President Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam has passed away, and President Obama has expressed his condolences on behalf of the American people. Dr. Kalam was a scientist and statesman who rose from humble beginnings to become a respected leader in India. He advocated for stronger U.S.-India relations and worked to deepen space cooperation between the two countries. Dr. Kalam's presidency saw significant growth in U.S.-India ties, and he was known as the "People's President" for his humility and dedication to public service. His life and work continue to inspire millions of Indians and admirers worldwide.